-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Compiling and executing the RLPN decoding algorithm (Algorithm 3.1 of the preprint)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

python compile_RLPN_decode.py
See compile_RLPN_decode.py for more information about what is implemented, how the parameters can be
changed.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
Producing a full text execution trace of the RLPN decoding algorithm
--------------------------------------------------------------------

python compile_RLPN_statistics.py
See compile_RLPN_statistics.py for more information about what is implemented, how the parameters can be
changed.

----------------------
Compiler requirements:
----------------------
g++ that supports -std=c++20

------------------------------------------
Compiler options that can be desactivated:
------------------------------------------

If openmp is not on your machine, or if you wish to desactivate it, it suffices to erase
 "-fopenmp" in the variable optim in the function compile in the file "compile_RLPN_decode.py" and "compile_RLPN_statistics.py".


